{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SnowLayerCombination",
        "description": "Combined-layer properties when two snow layers are merged (Oleson et al. 2010, Section 5.1.5.1, Eqs. 5.38–5.42). Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/hydrology.jl:253 (`SnowLayerCombination` @component). Observed-only: per-layer thicknesses, water/ice contents, and temperatures are inputs (parameters); combined thickness/water/ice/enthalpies/temperature are algebraic outputs.",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "hydrology",
            "snow",
            "observed-only",
            "oleson-2010"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-lgbd)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., Bonan, G. B., Feddema, J., Vertenstein, M., & Grimmond, C. S. B. (2010). Technical Description of an Urban Parameterization for the Community Land Model (CLMU). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-480+STR. Chapter 5, Section 5.1.5.1, Equations 5.38–5.42, p. 122."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SnowLayerCombination": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/hydrology.jl:253\nUpstream `SnowLayerCombination` is an MTK `@component` whose per-layer inputs (Δz_1, Δz_2, w_liq_1, w_liq_2, w_ice_1, w_ice_2, T_1, T_2) are `@parameters` and whose outputs (Δz_c, w_liq_c, w_ice_c, T_c, h_1, h_2) are time-indexed `@variables` with algebraic-only equations. Identical structure preserved here; the unicode `Δz` symbol is rendered as ASCII `Dz` (other ESM components in this rig use ASCII identifiers — see e.g. components/wildland_fire/terrain_slope.esm `tan_phi`). The upstream `@constants` block (T_f, L_f, C_ice, C_liq) is preserved as zero-tolerance parameters with the upstream default values; they are physical constants from Oleson 2010 Table 1.4 and are not intended to be tuned.\n\nThe combined-temperature equation T_c = T_f + (h_1 + h_2 - L_f * w_liq_c) / (C_ice * w_ice_c + C_liq * w_liq_c) requires a non-zero denominator C_ice * w_ice_c + C_liq * w_liq_c — i.e. the merged layer must contain at least some ice or liquid water. All test cases below preserve that invariant.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); the equations are products, sums, and one division — five floating-point operations on hardware-supported intrinsics — so float64 roundoff is ~1e-15. 1e-9 leaves comfortable headroom above ULP roundoff and is well below any plausible physical-discrimination scale on snow layer enthalpies (which are O(1e5–1e6 J/m^2) and combined temperatures (which carry K resolution ~1e-2 in practice)."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-9
            },
            "variables": {
                "T_f": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 273.15,
                    "description": "Freezing temperature of water (Oleson et al. 2010 Table 1.4)"
                },
                "L_f": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/kg",
                    "default": 333700.0,
                    "description": "Latent heat of fusion of water (Oleson et al. 2010 Table 1.4; 3.337e5 J/kg)"
                },
                "C_ice": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/kg/K",
                    "default": 2117.27,
                    "description": "Specific heat of ice (Oleson et al. 2010 Table 1.4)"
                },
                "C_liq": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/kg/K",
                    "default": 4188.0,
                    "description": "Specific heat of liquid water (Oleson et al. 2010 Table 1.4)"
                },
                "Dz_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.05,
                    "description": "Thickness of layer 1"
                },
                "Dz_2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.05,
                    "description": "Thickness of layer 2"
                },
                "w_liq_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Liquid water in layer 1"
                },
                "w_liq_2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Liquid water in layer 2"
                },
                "w_ice_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 5.0,
                    "description": "Ice content in layer 1"
                },
                "w_ice_2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 5.0,
                    "description": "Ice content in layer 2"
                },
                "T_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 270.0,
                    "description": "Temperature of layer 1"
                },
                "T_2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 270.0,
                    "description": "Temperature of layer 2"
                },
                "Dz_c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Combined thickness (Eq. 5.38)"
                },
                "w_liq_c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "description": "Combined liquid water (Eq. 5.39)"
                },
                "w_ice_c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "description": "Combined ice content (Eq. 5.40)"
                },
                "T_c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "K",
                    "description": "Combined temperature (Eq. 5.41)"
                },
                "h_1": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "J/m^2",
                    "description": "Enthalpy of layer 1 (Eq. 5.42)"
                },
                "h_2": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "J/m^2",
                    "description": "Enthalpy of layer 2 (Eq. 5.42)"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "Dz_c",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": ["Dz_1", "Dz_2"]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "w_liq_c",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": ["w_liq_1", "w_liq_2"]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "w_ice_c",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": ["w_ice_1", "w_ice_2"]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "h_1",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["C_ice", "w_ice_1"] },
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["C_liq", "w_liq_1"] }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": ["T_1", "T_f"]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": ["L_f", "w_liq_1"]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "h_2",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["C_ice", "w_ice_2"] },
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["C_liq", "w_liq_2"] }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": ["T_2", "T_f"]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": ["L_f", "w_liq_2"]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "T_c",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            "T_f",
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": ["h_1", "h_2"]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": ["L_f", "w_liq_c"]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["C_ice", "w_ice_c"] },
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["C_liq", "w_liq_c"] }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "equal_layers_isothermal_270K",
                    "description": "Two identical layers at 270 K. Combined T_c must equal each layer's T (no thermal mixing); combined Δz/w_liq/w_ice are simple sums; h_1 and h_2 must be equal.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.05, "Dz_2": 0.05,
                        "w_liq_1": 1.0, "w_liq_2": 1.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 5.0, "w_ice_2": 5.0,
                        "T_1": 270.0, "T_2": 270.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Dz_c",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.1 },
                        { "variable": "w_liq_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2.0 },
                        { "variable": "w_ice_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 10.0 },
                        { "variable": "h_1",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 287160.79750000034 },
                        { "variable": "h_2",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 287160.79750000034 },
                        { "variable": "T_c",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 270.0 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "upstream_test_reference",
                    "description": "Reproduces the parameter point used by the upstream Julia `SnowLayerCombination - Equation Verification` testitem (UrbanCanopy.jl test/hydrology_test.jl:571). Asymmetric layers (Δz, w_liq, w_ice, T all differ) — exercises the full mixing formula end-to-end.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.05, "Dz_2": 0.10,
                        "w_liq_1": 0.5, "w_liq_2": 1.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 3.0, "w_ice_2": 5.0,
                        "T_1": 270.0, "T_2": 265.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Dz_c",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.15000000000000002 },
                        { "variable": "w_liq_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.5 },
                        { "variable": "w_ice_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 8.0 },
                        { "variable": "h_1",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 140245.6985000002 },
                        { "variable": "h_2",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 213289.04750000034 },
                        { "variable": "T_c",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 266.8186373392776 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "freezing_isothermal",
                    "description": "Both layers at the freezing point (T_1 = T_2 = T_f = 273.15 K). The (T_i - T_f) term collapses to zero, leaving only the latent-heat term: h_i = L_f * w_liq_i. T_c = T_f exactly.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.05, "Dz_2": 0.05,
                        "w_liq_1": 1.0, "w_liq_2": 1.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 5.0, "w_ice_2": 5.0,
                        "T_1": 273.15, "T_2": 273.15
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h_1", "time": 0.0, "expected": 333700.0 },
                        { "variable": "h_2", "time": 0.0, "expected": 333700.0 },
                        { "variable": "T_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 273.15 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "no_liquid_cold",
                    "description": "Dry-snow regime: w_liq_1 = w_liq_2 = 0 (no latent-heat contribution). Mass-weighted temperature mixing reduces to T_c = T_f + (C_ice * (w_ice_1 * (T_1 - T_f) + w_ice_2 * (T_2 - T_f))) / (C_ice * w_ice_c) = T_f + ((10 * (-13.15) + 20 * (-23.15)) / 30) = 253.333... K. Exercises the C_liq * w_liq term collapsing to zero on both sides of the division.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.10, "Dz_2": 0.20,
                        "w_liq_1": 0.0, "w_liq_2": 0.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 10.0, "w_ice_2": 20.0,
                        "T_1": 260.0, "T_2": 250.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Dz_c",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.30000000000000004 },
                        { "variable": "w_liq_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "w_ice_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 30.0 },
                        { "variable": "h_1",     "time": 0.0, "expected": -278421.00499999954 },
                        { "variable": "h_2",     "time": 0.0, "expected": -980296.0099999991 },
                        { "variable": "T_c",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 253.33333333333331 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "no_ice_warm",
                    "description": "Slush/melt-pool regime: w_ice = 0 in both layers (only liquid water). The (h_1 + h_2 - L_f * w_liq_c) numerator cancels the latent-heat term, leaving the sensible-heat balance over C_liq alone. T_c collapses to the common T = 274 K.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.05, "Dz_2": 0.05,
                        "w_liq_1": 5.0, "w_liq_2": 5.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 0.0, "w_ice_2": 0.0,
                        "T_1": 274.0, "T_2": 274.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "w_ice_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "h_1",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 1686299.0000000005 },
                        { "variable": "h_2",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 1686299.0000000005 },
                        { "variable": "T_c",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 274.0 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "asymmetric_thickness",
                    "description": "Highly asymmetric thicknesses (Δz_1 = 0.02 m vs Δz_2 = 0.18 m, 9× ratio) with proportionally scaled water/ice contents (w_*_2 = 9 * w_*_1). The mass-weighted T_c lies near the temperature of the larger thermal mass (T_2 = 271 K) — exercises the heat-capacity-weighted mixing in the (h_1 + h_2)/(C_ice w_ice_c + C_liq w_liq_c) division.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.02, "Dz_2": 0.18,
                        "w_liq_1": 0.5, "w_liq_2": 4.5,
                        "w_ice_1": 2.0, "w_ice_2": 18.0,
                        "T_1": 268.0, "T_2": 271.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Dz_c",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.19999999999999998 },
                        { "variable": "w_liq_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.0 },
                        { "variable": "w_ice_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 20.0 },
                        { "variable": "h_1",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 134258.01900000015 },
                        { "variable": "h_2",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 1379192.7510000013 },
                        { "variable": "T_c",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 270.7 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "different_temps_equal_mass",
                    "description": "Equal-mass layers at different temperatures (T_1 = 268 K, T_2 = 272 K). Heat capacities cancel; T_c = (T_1 + T_2)/2 = 270 K. Cross-checks that the latent-heat term contributes equally to both numerator (via h_1, h_2) and the L_f * w_liq_c subtraction in the (h_1+h_2-L_f*w_liq_c) numerator.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.05, "Dz_2": 0.05,
                        "w_liq_1": 1.0, "w_liq_2": 1.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 5.0, "w_ice_2": 5.0,
                        "T_1": 268.0, "T_2": 272.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h_1", "time": 0.0, "expected": 257612.09750000032 },
                        { "variable": "h_2", "time": 0.0, "expected": 316709.49750000035 },
                        { "variable": "T_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 270.0 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "thick_warm_thin_cold",
                    "description": "Thin cold layer (Δz_1 = 0.01 m, T_1 = 265 K) merged with a thick warm layer (Δz_2 = 0.20 m, T_2 = 272.5 K). Combined T_c is heavily weighted toward the larger-mass warm layer (T_c ≈ 272.21 K, much closer to T_2 than to (T_1+T_2)/2 = 268.75 K). Exercises mass-weighted mixing across a 20× thickness ratio.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.01, "Dz_2": 0.20,
                        "w_liq_1": 0.1, "w_liq_2": 5.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 1.0, "w_ice_2": 20.0,
                        "T_1": 265.0, "T_2": 272.5
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Dz_c",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.21000000000000002 },
                        { "variable": "w_liq_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.1 },
                        { "variable": "w_ice_c", "time": 0.0, "expected": 21.0 },
                        { "variable": "h_1",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 12701.029500000055 },
                        { "variable": "h_2",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 1627364.4900000014 },
                        { "variable": "T_c",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 272.21102855952626 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "Tc_vs_T1_isothermal_pair_T2",
                    "description": "Sweep T_1 across the cold-snow range (250–273.15 K) at fixed T_2 = 270 K with equal-mass layers. The combined temperature traces the mass-weighted average — a straight line from (250, 260) to (273.15, 271.575) on the T_1 axis, demonstrating linear blending when the two heat capacities are matched.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.05, "Dz_2": 0.05,
                        "w_liq_1": 1.0, "w_liq_2": 1.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 5.0, "w_ice_2": 5.0,
                        "T_2": 270.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "T_1",
                                "range": { "start": 250.0, "stop": 273.15, "count": 24, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "Tc_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Combined temperature T_c as a function of layer-1 temperature T_1 at fixed T_2 = 270 K (equal-mass mixing).",
                            "x": { "variable": "T_1", "label": "Layer 1 temperature (K)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "T_c", "label": "Combined temperature (K)" }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "h1_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Layer-1 enthalpy h_1 as a function of layer-1 temperature — linear, with intercept set by the latent-heat term L_f * w_liq_1.",
                            "x": { "variable": "T_1", "label": "Layer 1 temperature (K)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "h_1", "label": "Layer 1 enthalpy (J/m^2)" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "Tc_heatmap_T1_T2",
                    "description": "Two-dimensional sweep over (T_1, T_2) covering the cold-snow range (250–273.15 K) — surfaces the planar mass-weighted T_c surface that drives the layer-merging step in the CLM4-Urban snow scheme.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "Dz_1": 0.05, "Dz_2": 0.05,
                        "w_liq_1": 1.0, "w_liq_2": 1.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 5.0, "w_ice_2": 5.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "T_1",
                                "range": { "start": 250.0, "stop": 273.15, "count": 12, "scale": "linear" }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "T_2",
                                "range": { "start": 250.0, "stop": 273.15, "count": 12, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "Tc_surface",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "Combined temperature T_c(T_1, T_2) for equal-mass layers — symmetric about the T_1 = T_2 diagonal.",
                            "x": { "variable": "T_1", "label": "Layer 1 temperature (K)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "T_2", "label": "Layer 2 temperature (K)" },
                            "value": { "variable": "T_c", "reduce": "final" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
